# This file is optional and, today, unused: Noticoel's infrastructure
# configuration (server, database, which notifiers are enabled, and their
# credentials) is read entirely from NOTICOEL_* environment variables —
# see the README's Configuration section.
#
# config/config.yaml is reserved for future business configuration that
# doesn't map cleanly onto environment variables (routing rules,
# notification templates...). None of that exists yet, so there is
# nothing to put here today.
#
# If you're upgrading from a pre-2.0 Noticoel and still have a
# config.yaml with `server:`, `database:` or `notifiers:` sections, it
# keeps working as a fallback for whichever environment variables you
# haven't set yet — but new deployments don't need this file at all.
#
# To use this file, copy it to config.yaml (gitignored, like .env).
